    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "well yeah i know the official line is that everything is transparent, but that's exactly why i'm asking. if they wanted to hide something they wouldn't leave a giant hole, they'd just fill it with mundane data to make it look normal. look at the way certain telemetry gaps appear in the lunar module descent phases or how certain high-res photos from the lunar surface were 'lost' or 'degraded' over time. it doesn't feel like accidents, it feels like a cleanup. don't you think it's a bit too convenient that so much original data is missing or unreadable now?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
